snippet.textDisplay:
ONE SUGGESTION : IF Coke studio is open to FEEDBACK.

1. SHOULD HAVE USED ONLY RAJASTHANI 

The song is good however , when two strong languages are used , Rajasthani and Punjabi , rather than complementing , they act against each other.

Punjabi is a strong language , so is rajasthani ,
In my opinion just using one language is better than using 2 strong languages together in one song.

If you listen to Rajasthani songs alone , the whole song is full of Rajasthani spirit.You enjoy the song better.You are lost in the images of Rajasthan.

A song with just Rajasthani Folk would have alone brought a lot of Mystic and desert like feel to the song .

A neutral language like Hindi along with Rajasthani would have complemented beautifully .

Hence rather than rajasthani + Punjabi , it should have been 
Rajasthani+ Hindi


2. NASEEBO LAAL , is a very good find , never heard her , her accent and command on rajasthani is very good.

Would like to hear more from her alone .

3. UMER was as good as he is , his style is amazing , once during the song , his voice cracked up on a higher pitch , a similar attempt while singing , "SAMMI MERI WAAR" , higher pitch was achieved beautifully , but then this is totally excusable.

I feel his style, personality did not come out well in this song.

THIS SONG SHOULD HAVE BEEN SOLELY CONCENTRATING ON this female Rajasthani Singer.

5/10 FOR THIS SONG.

Over all great music guys , as always , great talent.
I will follow SHIRAZ UPPAL more , to see what more of Rajasthani gems he is able to bring out ..:)


PLEASE BRING OUT more of FOLK from your area. would really be nice.
Rajasthani fusion is lacking at your end, would like your team to experiment , UNEARTH it more.
